{"type":"step-attempt","step":"cross-boundary-invariants","sessionId":"ead3d8b6-c58e-4401-bee5-66cafef993af","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/sequential-single-writer/cross-boundary-invariants-result-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[{"severity":"medium","resolution":"fixable","file":"src/core/step/executor-helpers.ts","title":"B-13 guard blind spot: dead-code functions with direct store mutations remain","rationale":"failStepWithError (store.fail + store.persist) and createSessionWithHistory (store.appendHistory + store.update + store.fail) are dead code with zero callers. B-13's grep guard is scoped to direct call-sites in executor.ts. If either function were re-imported into executor.ts or sibling core/step/ code, the store.* calls in executor-helpers.ts would not be detected by B-13, silently bypassing the ratified invariant. The ratification claim has a structural gap proportional to this orphaned code."},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"src/core/step/commit-orchestrator.ts","title":"Implicit invariant: CLI steps cannot be skipped is not structurally enforced","rationale":"apply() dispatches commitSkipped(step as AgentStep, ...) relying on the implicit invariant that only agent steps produce kind:'skipped'. runCliStep currently has no activation check so this cannot occur, but the cast hides the type gap. A future addition of activation logic to CLI steps would silently pass the cast and call commitSkipped with a CliStep.","line":362}],"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"src/core/pipeline/pipeline.ts","title":"Pipeline safety-net store.fail uses pre-begin state — pre-existing race","rationale":"When execute() throws without .state attached (unexpected bug), the pipeline safety net calls store.fail(pre-begin-state). At this point begin() has already written {step}-started to disk; the safety net overwrites with a failed version of the pre-begin state. This was identical behavior before the change and is not a regression.","line":276},{"severity":"low","file":"src/core/step/commit-orchestrator.ts","title":"Double-persist for sequential steps is idempotent","rationale":"CommitOrchestrator.commitSuccess/commitSkipped persists, then pipeline.ts line 289 also persists (crash-resilience). For halt paths, commitHalt persists then the pipeline re-persists err.state. All double-persists are idempotent and the design explicitly retains pipeline-level crash-resilience out of scope."}]},"followUpAttempts":1,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-07-13T18:22:46.611Z","endedAt":"2026-07-13T18:31:11.484Z"}
